The paper discusses information theoretic security, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). It also mentions coding and wiretap coding, which are related to cryptography (cs.CR). The use of randomness and hash families is also relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY). The paper may also be relevant to multimedia security (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI) due to the discussion of transmission codes.
